{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"135496e6-b5ff-4873-85a9-74b85a719d21","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. `Category` trait → `category` (lowercase)\nMTP's filter engine is **case-sensitive** for trait names. xUnit v3 maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` but the filter key must be lowercase `category`.\n\n### 2. `&` operator → `&` or `and`\nThe `&` syntax still works, but some MTP versions prefer the explicit `and` keyword.\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n| Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)                               | New (MTP / xUnit v3)                                  |\n|-------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke`  | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and category=Smoke` |\n\nThe key gotcha: **`Category=Smoke`** silently matches nothing in MTP because trait filtering is case-sensitive — it must be **`category=Smoke`** (lowercase key, original-case value).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"515fec99-cf18-41c5-b191-d72fd3c752db","outputTokens":279,"requestId":"67C4:13C959:29B17E1:2E19F11:69FD379F"},"id":"443a74aa-2a2a-4ec8-a521-905c1455b120","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:08:55.137Z","parentId":"13148b7a-e8dd-4807-b9fd-f0285a20befb"}
